description: Following the Kryptonian purge of Metropolis' super-villain population Superman confronts an unrepentant Alura who explains her intentions for the worlds stored on Brainiac's ship.
name: New Krypton, Part 7 - Brainiac Lives

description: A witch cult has one of the Ancient Old Ones and keeps it bound and tortured, trying to wrest its secrets. Only Henry Said, student of the Necronomicon, can save the Earth from the cult- but in doing so, will surely unleash the vengeance of the Old Ones!

SPOTLIGHT ON RUSTY!

Years ago, Rusty was mortally wounded and Doc saved his son's life by placing his brain into a robotic body. But lately, Rusty's been acting more and more like a robot. Is he losing his humanity? Or is he falling victim to an evil plot? Find out in this issue!
name: Old Feelings

description:
The White House has an unexpected guest! The Scooby Gang will have to find the secret behind the Wicked Witch of the West Wing before the government gets scared silly!

  • Dead & Let Spy
  • The Ghostly Fruit Stand
  • Picture This Mystery
  • The Dragon In The Bathroom
  • Danger-Prone Daphne
name: Dead & Let Spy; The Ghostly Fruit Stand; Picture This Mystery; The Dragon In The Bathroom; Danger-Prone Daphne

description: Ever have one of those days where your world feels like it's falling apart? Well, Apropos is having one right now, except it's literal. With the world coming apart around him, Apropos finds himself entering a bizarre land where creatures of the night roam and Apropos is thrust into the strange role of slayer and hero to the people, a role in which he has no interest... unless he's offered the right price.
name: Gypsies, Vamps And Thieves Part Two

description: It just wouldn't be Christmas without the Punisher, now would it? There's no room at the inn for a mobster and his pregnant wife who are on the run from rival gangsters, but lucky for them Frank Castle is in a giving mood. Though keeping them alive won't be easy, what with three vicious gun-toting wise-guys and a wacked-out pimp named Shepherd all hot on their trail. But then nobody ever said Christmas miracles came easy, did they?
name: And On Earth Peace, Good Will Toward Men

description: In the timeless realm of Japanese myth, the King of Dreams has told the fox how to save the life of the human she loves. It's simple: To protect him, she has to die in his place. In the uncertain realm of dreams and nightmares...

"Cold Case" Part 1 of 3

A journalist has researched the identity of the Gotham Ripper, a mad serial killer and the evidence points to Thomas Wayne! Can Batman clear his father's name? Things get more confusing when the journalist turns up dead!
name: Cold Case Part 1 of 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
The UNIVERSE X spotlight swings on the Master of Magnetism! On a planet where everyone is a mutant, can Magneto be a hero? Like the 4, SPIDEY, and the BEASTS specials, this one-shot expands the world of EARTH X!

Takes place between Universe X #11 and 12

The fourth of six self-contained stories written by Warren Ellis (THE AUTHORITY, TRANSMETROPOLITAN) and illustrated by a surprising array of artists features two very different ghost stories. In "Setting Sun," illustrated by Javier Pulido, Constantine may be the only hope of absolution for the restless spirit of a Japanese surgeon guilty of ungodly atrocities. And in "One Last Love Song," illustrated by James Romberger (FLINCH), a late-night pub crawl takes an unforeseen twist.

Reprinted in: Hellblazer : Setting Sun (2004)
name: Telling Tales

description: For once, the heroes of Knothill Village have a chance to relax and enjoy a nice quiet picnic together... yeah, right! Things go from picnic to panic when Chuck spots a meteor hurtling toward earth -- and it has an Chaos Emerald embedded inside! Now the heroes must travel to the South Pole and keep Eggman from getting his hands on it. To make things more interesting, they decide make it a competition and split up into teams. Before they're through, readers will witness more action, romance, and inter-squad squabbling to rival a certain fantastic foursome!
name: Meteor Madness

Featuring Wolverine, Spider-Girl, Killraven, Hyperion, Bloodstorm, Deathlok and the Iron Man of 2020!
name: Chapter Two

description: This three-issue prelude to PARADISE X concludes as X-51's ragtag band of alternate reality heroes face their ultimate adversary -- the threat of the Celestial Embryos! Will even the combined forces of Wolverine, Machine Man, Iron Man 2020, Bloodstorm, Hyperion, Deathlok, Killraven, and Spider-Girl be enough to save the multiverse?

description:
1920's prohibition era Chicago. Al Capone heads the largest, most powerful mafia organization in the country. Business is good so good that a certain bloodsucker from Transylvania has his sights set on a

piece of the pie. Capone must team up with unlikely allies Elliot Ness and The Untouchables to save the city from the biggest bloodbath the world has ever seen.

Zen and Nira-X are hired by three of the richest people in the universe to retrieve an orb of unimaginable power from an evil section of space, called Hellspace. But when Nira-X discovers the true nature of the orb, will she retrieve it or destroy it?

Jason Voorhees's return to Crystal Lake finds him stalking a young woman. But as it turns out she is stalking him, and as he chases her, they enter a fairly open part of the surrounding forest. Surprise: a FBI assualt team is waiting for Jason. They open fire and kill the undead maniac. Or did they?

volume.name: Jason Goes to Hell the Final Friday
Jason Goes to Hell the Final Friday
Jason Goes to Hell the Final Friday

description: Journey back to a time when magic still thrived, dragons and fallen gods roamed the earth and man was just a myth. The Garden of Eden was a place of perfect peace and tranquility. That is, until its keeper, Adam, went missing. Now, his newly created wife, Eve, must venture outside the safety of the Garden for the first time to go in search of her husband, all the while battling monsters, beast men, wizards, demons, and even the gods themselves.
Eve has begun her quest to find the missing Adam, but it seems that someone is determined to stop her, forcing Eve to face her first true test - to battle with an army of soulless Golems!!

Eve continues her quest and gains an unusual ally - the mystery man known only as Mel the Barbarian. But is he human, angel, demon, or something else entirely? And, Eve has her first encounter with the mysterious Watchers and learns some startling secrets about her origins.
The conclusion! Eve faces the ultimate test as she finally comes face to face with Adam's abductor. But when the dust settles, will her reunion with her husband be a happy one?

"Paging Count Dracula"

"Take Me Out to the Ballgame"
name: Paging Count Dracula / Take Me Out to the Ballgame

volume.name: The New Adventures Of The Toxic Avenger

description:
It's 1986, and Ronald Reagan's cabinet is in a meeting discussing how to curtail the threat of a nuclear holocaust on the United States by the World Terrorist Organization (WTO). A terrorist car bomb was set off in Paris, and the next day Reagan and his cabinet are led by Colonel Armour to a top secret facility located underground known as Project Alpha-Soldier. Through use of genetic engineering, they are told that the human body can be changed and given super-strength and great vitality. It's revealed that the machine works best on the elderly, and that younger people who went through the process degenerated to the point of turning into dust after a short amount of time. It is hinted that the elderly that had survived the initial testing process were then killed in staged automobile accidents. Reagan, anxious to combat terrorism, decides he will go through the process, as well as his cabinet.

While this was happening, the soviet Omegus and his cyborg lackeys Angel and Scythe are going over the plans to cause a meltdown to occur at a nuclear power plant, while making it seem like they are doing the same to two other plants. The first two are decoys, while the last one will be the actual target.

Scythe and his team begin an attack at a dam somewhere in Pennsylvania, where he discovers the mole working against them known as Needle. When Scythe throws the spy off the dam, Reagan and his Raiders leap and rappel out of a helicopter to come to the rescue. Reagan saves Needle, and while the rest of the Raiders are taking care of the terrorists, Scythe and Reagan become locked in combat. During the battle, a conduit was damaged and began letting hot steam escape, which began to melt Scythe and killed him.

Later, Needle informs them that there are two other targets that the terrorists are going after. The Raiders hop in their helicopter and head to the next target; Seegram's Nuclear Power Station. Angel and two other terrorists are at this location, and, being enraged by the news of Scythe's death, begins to damage the cooling system for the reactor to cause a meltdown so that she and the others can die for their cause. When the Raiders get there, Angel is about to cause the whole place to destruct. The other two terrorist that were with her get cold feet, and tackle her. This causes her power supply to short circuit, which in turn makes her disintegrate.

After hearing that both of his main henchmen were dead, Omegus makes his way to the Willow Nuclear Power Plant and hand drops a bomb towards it. Ronald Reagan and and his vice president rocket-pack into action, and Ronald grabs the rocket and gives it to George Bush, telling him to secure the bomb while he takes care of Omegus. Omegus then shoots a rocket launcher at Reagan, which only knocks him back upon impact. Reagan climbs to the top of the helicopter and stops the blades from rotating at the base using his hands, and uses his rocket pack to guide the helicopter into the nuclear stack, causing Omegus and the helicopter to explode as Reagan flies away.
name: Back To Zero
